The '''rufous-throated flycatcher''' ('''''Ficedula rufigula''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Muscicapidae]]. It is [[endemic]] to [[Sulawesi]], [[Indonesia]]. Its natural [[habitat]] is subtropical or tropical moist lowland [[forest]]s. It is threatened by [[habitat loss]].

